<paragraph blockId="8.[347,1254,1726,1777]" pageId="8" pageNumber="785">
D e s c r i p t i o n: External morphology as in 
<taxonomicName authority="PACE. Distinguished" authorityName="PACE. Distinguished" authorityYear="1996" box="[858,1167,1726,1748]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="785" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icaria">
<emphasis box="[858,951,1727,1748]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="785">G. icaria</emphasis>
PACE. Distinguished
</taxonomicName>
only by the primary sexual characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[783,819,357,378]" box="[783,819,357,378]" pageId="9" pageNumber="786">786</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[347,1254,432,483]" pageId="9" pageNumber="786">
: tergite VIII and sternite VIII as in 
<figureCitation box="[755,870,432,454]" captionStart="Figs 22-34" captionStartId="9.[347,387,1682,1702]" captionTargetBox="[348,1247,497,1652]" captionTargetId="figure-42@9.[347,1260,718,1197]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 22-34: Geostiba atrioculata nov.sp. (22-23) and G. albimontis nov.sp. (24-34): (22-23, 33-34) spermatheca; (23) male tergite VIII; (25) male sternite VIII; (26-28) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (29-30) internal spines of median lobe in lateral and in ventral view; (31) female tergite VIII; (32) female sternite VIII. Scale bars: 24-25, 31-32: 0.2 mm; 22-23, 26-30, 33-34: 0.1 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="786">Figs 24-25</figureCitation>
; median lobe of aedeagus of similar morphology as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="PACE. Distinguished" authorityYear="1996" box="[531,622,462,483]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="786" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icaria">
<emphasis box="[531,622,462,483]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="786">G. icaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but with two long spines in internal sac (
<figureCitation box="[1046,1160,461,483]" captionStart="Figs 22-34" captionStartId="9.[347,387,1682,1702]" captionTargetBox="[348,1247,497,1652]" captionTargetId="figure-42@9.[347,1260,718,1197]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 22-34: Geostiba atrioculata nov.sp. (22-23) and G. albimontis nov.sp. (24-34): (22-23, 33-34) spermatheca; (23) male tergite VIII; (25) male sternite VIII; (26-28) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (29-30) internal spines of median lobe in lateral and in ventral view; (31) female tergite VIII; (32) female sternite VIII. Scale bars: 24-25, 31-32: 0.2 mm; 22-23, 26-30, 33-34: 0.1 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="786">Figs 26-30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
